<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=yes">
    <title>SecureCodeHub | Cybersecurity Learning Hub</title>
    <style>
        /* Reset default browser margins and padding for consistent rendering */
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        /* Body styling with gradient background matching SecureCodeHub theme */
        body {
            background: linear-gradient(145deg, #f0f4f8 0%, #e6edf4 100%);
            font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            min-height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
        }
        img {
            width: 60%;
            min-width: 300px;
            max-height: 500px;
            height: auto;
        }

        /* Main container to center and constrain content width */
        .hub-container {
            max-width: 1300px;
            width: 100%;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        /* Header area styling */
        .hero {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
        }

        /* Main title with gradient text effect */
        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0B2B3F, #1C587A);
            background-clip: text;
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            color: transparent;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            text-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.02);
        }

        /* Tagline/subtitle styling */
        .hero .tagline {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: #2c5a7a;
            margin-top: 0.6rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(28, 88, 122, 0.25);
            display: inline-block;
            padding-bottom: 0.3rem;
        }

        /* Purpose section - explains website mission */
        .purpose-section {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 1.8rem 2rem;
            margin: 1rem 0 2rem 0;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03), 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
            border: 1px solid rgba(28, 88, 122, 0.2);
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
        }

        /* Inner container for purpose section content */
        .purpose-inner {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Purpose section title styling */
        .purpose-title {
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #0B2B3F;
            letter-spacing: -0.3px;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.6rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        /* Circular icon next to purpose title */
        .purpose-title span {
            background: #0B2B3F;
            color: white;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            width: 36px;
            height: 36px;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            border-radius: 50%;
        }

        /* Purpose text paragraph styling */
        .purpose-text {
            font-size: 1.08rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
            color: #1f3b4c;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        /* Highlight box at bottom of purpose section */
        .purpose-highlight {
            background: #eef4fc;
            padding: 0.8rem 1.2rem;
            border-radius: 1.5rem;
            display: inline-block;
            margin-top: 0.8rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: #0e5a7c;
            border-left: 3px solid #1C7EB5;
        }

        /* Security Tip of the Day section */
        .tip-section {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0B2B3F, #1C587A);
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
            margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem 0;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            border: 1px solid rgba(28, 126, 181, 0.3);
            text-align: center;
        }

        .tip-section .tip-icon {
            font-size: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .tip-section .tip-label {
            color: #8ab3cf;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 2px;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        .tip-section .tip-text {
            color: white;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            font-weight: 400;
        }

        .tip-section .tip-text::before {
            content: '"';
        }

        .tip-section .tip-text::after {
            content: '"';
        }

        /* Grid container for the feature cards */
        .paths-grid {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 2rem;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: stretch;
            margin: 2rem 0 2rem;
        }

        /* Individual card styling */
        .path-card {
            flex: 1;
            min-width: 260px;
            max-width: 340px;
            background: #FFFFFF;
            backdrop-filter: blur(0px);
            border-radius: 2rem;
            box-shadow: 0 12px 28px -8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
            transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.9, 0.4, 1.1);
            border: 1px solid rgba(28, 88, 122, 0.2);
            overflow: hidden;
            color: #0B2B3F;
        }

        /* Card hover effect - lifts card and adds shadow */
        .path-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-6px);
            box-shadow: 0 24px 40px -14px rgba(12, 52, 78, 0.2);
            border-color: #1C7EB5;
            background: #FFFFFF;
        }

        /* Makes entire card clickable */
        .card-link {
            text-decoration: none;
            display: block;
            padding: 2rem 1.5rem 2rem 1.5rem;
            height: 100%;
            width: 100%;
            color: inherit;
        }

        /* Icon container for each card */
        .path-icon {
            font-size: 2.6rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            display: inline-block;
            background: #eef2fa;
            padding: 0.5rem 0.8rem;
            border-radius: 1.2rem;
            line-height: 1;
            color: #1C7EB5;
        }

        /* Card title styling */
        .path-title {
            font-size: 1.7rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            margin: 0.5rem 0 0.7rem;
            letter-spacing: -0.3px;
            color: #0B2B3F;
        }

        /* Card description text */
        .path-desc {
            color: #2c556e;
            line-height: 1.5;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
        }

        /* Arrow indicator at bottom of card */
        .path-arrow {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.4rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: #1C7EB5;
            border-bottom: 1.5px solid #c6dcec;
            transition: gap 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
        }

        /* Arrow animation on card hover */
        .path-card:hover .path-arrow {
            gap: 0.7rem;
            border-bottom-color: #1C7EB5;
        }

        /* Decorative divider line */
        .divider {
            width: 70px;
            height: 3px;
            background: linear-gradient(90deg, #1C7EB5, #70b8e0, #1C7EB5);
            border-radius: 3px;
            margin: 0.7rem auto 0;
        }

        /* Information note at bottom of content area */
        .info-note {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: #3d6a87;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
            padding: 0.6rem 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 40px;
            display: inline-block;
            backdrop-filter: blur(2px);
        }

        /* FAQ / Information section styling */
        .info-section {
            background: white;
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 2.5rem;
            margin: 2rem 0 1rem 0;
            box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
            border: 1px solid rgba(28, 88, 122, 0.2);
        }

        .info-section h3 {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #0B2B3F;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            letter-spacing: -0.3px;
        }

        /* Vertical list layout for info cards */
        .info-list {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }

        .info-card {
            background: #f8fafd;
            border-radius: 1.5rem;
            padding: 1.8rem 2rem;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
            border-left: 4px solid #1C7EB5;
        }

        .info-card:hover {
            transform: translateX(6px);
            background: #eef4fc;
        }

        .info-card h4 {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #0B2B3F;
            margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
        }

        .info-card p {
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #2c556e;
        }

        .stat-number {
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: #1C7EB5;
            display: inline-block;
            margin-right: 5px;
        }

        .stat-highlight {
            background: #eef4fc;
            padding: 1rem;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin-top: 0.8rem;
            border-left: 3px solid #c0392b;
        }

        .stat-highlight p {
            margin: 0;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: #1f3b4c;
        }

        /* Footer section */
        footer {
            margin-top: 2rem;
            text-align: center;
            width: 100%;
            border-top: 1px solid rgba(28, 88, 122, 0.15);
            padding-top: 1.2rem;
        }

        /* Footer text styling */
        .footer-text {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: #4f7b9a;
            letter-spacing: 0.3px;
        }

        /* Responsive styles for tablets and smaller screens */
        @media (max-width: 750px) {
            body { padding: 1.5rem 1rem; }
            .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
            .paths-grid { gap: 1.2rem; }
            .path-card { min-width: 240px; }
            .purpose-title { font-size: 1.35rem; }
            .purpose-text { font-size: 0.98rem; }
            .info-section { padding: 1.5rem; }
            .info-card { padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; }
            .info-card h4 { font-size: 1.1rem; }
            .info-card p { font-size: 0.9rem; }
            .tip-section .tip-text { font-size: 1rem; }
        }

        /* Responsive styles for mobile devices */
        @media (max-width: 550px) {
            .path-title { font-size: 1.45rem; }
            .card-link { padding: 1.3rem 1rem; }
            .purpose-section { padding: 1.2rem 1rem; }
            .info-card h4 { font-size: 1rem; }
            .tip-section { padding: 1rem 1.2rem; }
            .tip-section .tip-text { font-size: 0.9rem; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="hub-container">
    <!-- Hero section with main title and tagline -->
    <div class="hero">
        <img src="/images/logo3.png" alt="SecureCodeHub logo">
        <div class="tagline">build · defend · advance</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Purpose section explaining website mission -->
    <div class="purpose-section">
        <div class="purpose-inner">
            <div class="purpose-title">
                <span>⚡</span> Why SecureCodeHub?
            </div>
            <div class="purpose-text">
                In today's digital landscape, understanding security is not optional — it's essential.
                <strong>SecureCodeHub</strong> provides a structured, hands-on environment where developers, students,
                and security enthusiasts learn real-world cybersecurity concepts, from core principles to
                advanced vulnerability analysis.
            </div>
            <div class="purpose-text" style="margin-top: 0.6rem;">
                🎯 Our mission: demystify application security, promote secure coding habits, and empower you
                to identify, prevent, and mitigate threats — all in one clear, accessible hub.
            </div>
            <div class="purpose-highlight">
                📘 Learn core topics · 🔍 Explore vulnerability library · 🧠 Find out where to start using our chatbot · 🔎 Scan websites for vulnerabilities
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Security Tip of the Day -->
    <% if (typeof securityTip !== 'undefined' && securityTip) { %>
    <div class="tip-section">
        <div class="tip-icon">💡</div>
        <div class="tip-label">Security Tip of the Day</div>
        <div class="tip-text"><%= securityTip %></div>
    </div>
    <% } %>

    <!-- Grid of navigation cards -->
    <div class="paths-grid">
        <!-- Security Topics - links to topics page -->
        <div class="path-card">
            <a href="/topics" class="card-link" aria-label="Go to Main Learning Path – comprehensive security curriculum">
                <div class="path-icon">📘</div>
                <div class="path-title">Security Topics</div>
                <div class="path-desc">Master essential security topics: threat modeling, cryptography, secure design, OWASP fundamentals & more.</div>
                <span class="path-arrow">explore security topics →</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Vulnerability Library Card - links to vulnerabilities page -->
        <div class="path-card">
            <a href="/vuln" class="card-link" aria-label="Go to Vulnerability Library – detailed weakness database">
                <div class="path-icon">🐞</div>
                <div class="path-title">Vulnerability Library</div>
                <div class="path-desc">Deep dive into real security flaws: SQLi, XSS, CSRF, broken access control, and how attackers exploit them.</div>
                <span class="path-arrow">explore vulnerability library →</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- AI Chatbot Card - links to AI assistant page -->
        <div class="path-card">
            <a href="/chat" class="card-link" aria-label="Go to AI Chatbot – personalized guidance">
                <div class="path-icon">🧠</div>
                <div class="path-title">AI Help</div>
                <div class="path-desc">Don't know where to start? No problem! you can start by using our ai chatbot to find out where to start and what you need to secure your website.</div>
                <span class="path-arrow">Chat with our chatbot →</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Vulnerability Scanner Card - links to scanner page -->
        <div class="path-card">
            <a href="/scanner" class="card-link" aria-label="Go to Website Vulnerability Scanner">
                <div class="path-icon">🔎</div>
                <div class="path-title">Vulnerability Scanner</div>
                <div class="path-desc">Scan any website for security vulnerabilities. Enter a URL and get a detailed report of potential security issues.</div>
                <span class="path-arrow">scan a website →</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ / Information Section - Vertical Layout -->
    <div class="info-section">
        <h3>📚 Learn the Basics</h3>
        <div class="info-list">
            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>🛡️ What is Cybersecurity?</h4>
                <p>Cybersecurity is the practice of protecting systems, networks, programs, and data from digital attacks, damage, or unauthorized access. It encompasses everything from securing user credentials to defending entire corporate infrastructures against sophisticated cyber threats.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>⚠️ Why Cybersecurity Matters?</h4>
                <p>Data breaches cost companies millions in recovery, legal fees, and lost revenue — not to mention the irreversible damage to customer trust and brand reputation. In 2023 alone, over 8 billion records were exposed worldwide. With more businesses moving online, the attack surface continues to grow, making security everyone's responsibility.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>🐛 What is a Vulnerability?</h4>
                <p>A vulnerability is a weakness or flaw in a system's design, implementation, or configuration that can be exploited by attackers. Think of it as an unlocked back door — vulnerabilities give attackers a way in. They can exist in code, network settings, authentication mechanisms, or even in how users interact with a system.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>❓ Why Do Vulnerabilities Occur?</h4>
                <p>Vulnerabilities arise from many sources: coding mistakes (like forgetting to validate input), design flaws (poor authentication architecture), misconfigurations (default passwords left unchanged), outdated dependencies (unpatched libraries), and human error (weak passwords, phishing). Even time itself creates vulnerabilities as new attack methods are discovered.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>💻 What is Secure Coding?</h4>
                <p>Secure coding is the practice of writing software that is resistant to attacks. It means validating all user inputs, encoding outputs to prevent injection attacks, implementing proper authentication and authorization, managing sessions securely, encrypting sensitive data, logging appropriately without exposing secrets, and staying current with security best practices throughout the entire development lifecycle.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>📊 Security Statistics</h4>
                <p><span class="stat-number">93%</span> of company networks are vulnerable to breaches.<br>
                <span class="stat-number">43%</span> of data breaches target small businesses.<br>
                <span class="stat-number">$4.45M</span> average cost of a data breach in 2023.<br>
                <span class="stat-number">82%</span> of breaches involve the human element (phishing, weak passwords, misdelivery).</p>
                <div class="stat-highlight">
                    <p>⚠️ <strong>The hard truth:</strong> Most breaches are entirely preventable. Studies show that over 90% of successful cyberattacks could have been avoided with basic security measures — input validation, proper authentication, timely patching, and employee training. The knowledge you need is accessible. You just need to learn it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-card">
                <h4>👥 About Us</h4>
                <p>SecureCodeHub was created to bridge the gap between developers and security knowledge. We believe that security should be accessible to everyone, not just security professionals. Our platform is built by developers, for developers — with a focus on practical, real-world security concepts that you can immediately apply to your projects. Whether you're a beginner looking to understand the basics or an experienced developer wanting to deepen your security knowledge, SecureCodeHub is here to guide you every step of the way.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Information note at bottom of content -->
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
        <div class="info-note">
            💡 Start anywhere — each path adapts to your knowledge level.
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Footer section -->
<footer>
    <p class="footer-text">🔐 SecureCodeHub — Empowering developers to build resilient systems | © 2025</p>
</footer>
</body>
</html>
